The paper deals with the complexity of consistent query answering on databases, which is a topic closely related to database theory and query processing. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves complexity theory and logic, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also mentions stratified Datalog, which is a type of database query language, indicating that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implications of its findings, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well.
